{
    "description": "The difference between the simple pill navigation and the sliding pill nav is that the orange selected indicator is seperate, and thus can be animated.  In your component code, you need to adjust the width and translation of the otknav-pills-bar.",
    "html": "<!-- Use nav tag if the pills are a significant navigation block,\nuse a div otherwise -->\n<nav class=\"otknavbar\" role=\"navigation\">\n    <ul class=\"otknav otknav-pills\">\n        <li class=\"otkpill\">\n            <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\">Media</a>\n        </li>\n        <li class=\"otkpill otkpill-active\">\n            <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\">Friends Who Play</a>\n        </li>\n        <li class=\"otkpill\">\n            <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\">Compare Editions</a>\n        </li>\n    </ul>\n    <!-- for a sliding nav, you need to update the width and then transform the location\n    of the pills bar when you select a new tab.  Again this is component code to update\n    the position and width of the bar -->\n    <div class=\"otknav-pills-bar\" style=\"width: 121px; transform: translate3d(70px, 0px, 0px);\"></div>\n</nav>"
}